Remarks:
[Hardware] Procurement and installation of Anti-Jam (AJ) Global Positioning System (GPS) user equipment and prevention equipment is required to ensure the continued utility of GPS signals from space in
a hostile jamming environment. Sea NAVWAR will procure and field dual Advanced Digital Antenna Production (ADAP) Fiber Optic Antenna Link (FOAL) antennas. The Sea Navigation Warfare (NAVWAR)
program will equip ships with AJ GPS antennas to ensure the continued availability of GPS to support surface combat operations and provide reliable GPS and other navigation sensor data to ship-board
Command, Control, Communications, Computers, Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (C4ISR), Combat, and Weapons Systems.

(†)
      indicates the presence of a P-5a

Footnotes:
(1)
    NAVWAR MSC (ADAP): 1) In FY 2025, the Sea NAVWAR Anti Jam ADAP antenna incurred a pricing increase of approximately 68% with follow on price escalations reaching to 88% higher than the FY 2024
pricing. This price re-negotiation is primarily due to Raytheon Systems LTD UK having their first opportunity to adjust pricing since the pre-COVID era 2019 ADAP 5-Year Framework pricing was established.
The vendor experienced a significant increase in material costs since the original pricing was established in 2018 due to COVID era supply chain shortages, increased inflation, and tariffs. Additionally, actual
engineering hours required for ADAP production have increased, as validated by a Mechanization of Contract Administration Services (MOCAS) audit on behalf of DCMA. These increases, coupled with
smaller contributing factors, necessitate adjusted pricing. 2) Military Sealift Command (MSC) requires a single ADAP shipset which consists of one ADAP antenna and install. A single ADAP may range in cost
from $268K to $300K depending on the Economic Order Quantity Pricing and International exchange rates relevant at time of contract award. Funding for Military Sealift Command (MSC) procurements and
installations correspond with concurrent Global Positioning System (GPS) based Position Navigation and Timing System (GPNTS) procurements and installations. 3) Military Sealift Command (MSC) installation
costs have risen significantly due to factors including: last minute finalization of Military Sealift Command (MSC) availability locations (30 days prior) which increase Fleet Installation Office estimates; alteration
installation team expenses increase due to short time frame required for travel, per diem, and expedited shipping of government furnished equipment (GFE). Outside continental United States (OCONUS) work
further contributes to overall expense increases. Finally, increased Government Installation Contract (GIC) costs, likely stemming from labor shortages and general inflationary pressures, are driving up the price
of both parts and labor.
(2)
   NAVWAR (ADAP) DSA: Pre-Installation Design Services Allocation (DSA) are required in order to complete ship check and installation drawings for installation planning and is performed 6-12 months prior to
installation start. Post Installation DSA support requirements include drawings closeout. DSA costs will fluctuate each Fiscal Year as it is a factor of the number of installations in any given fiscal year.
(3)
    NAVWAR MSC (ADAP) 1)DSA: Pre-Installation Design Services Allocation (DSA) are required in order to complete ship check and installation drawings for installation planning and is performed 6-12 months
prior to installation start. Post Installation DSA support requirements include drawings closeout. DSA costs will fluctuate each Fiscal Year as it is a factor of the number of installations and platform in any given
fiscal year.



