INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L054$$, 2027, $$Global Positioning System (GPS)-based Positioning, Navigation, & Timing Service (GPNTS): The GPS-based PNT Service (GPNTS) system is the primary PNT system for the Navy to ensure reliable PNT
 capability and interoperability insertion in GPS receivers and associated Command, Control, Computers, Communications and Intelligence (C4I) and Combat Systems in a denied environment. GPNTS provides
 more robust and secure GPS/PNT capabilities than is currently in the Fleet. GPNTS provides precise PNT data required for combat, weapons, command, control, communications, navigation, and other systems,
 as well as providing the time synchronization critical to the network environments. GPNTS backfits existing PNT/GPS systems and forward fits new platforms. GPNTS is an Open Architecture (OA) development,
 enabling rapid software and hardware-based capability improvements to be inserted without a requirement for single-source contracting. GPNTS will host the US Space Force developed Military GPS User
 Equipment (MGUE) card, allowing access to the new more accurate and secure GPS Military-Code (M-Code) signal. GPNTS also provides the capability to migrate non-real time GPS data toward a Common
 Computing Environment (CCE) and provide a path for the integration of advanced navigation systems and sensors.

 The Global Positioning System (GPS)-based Position, Navigation, & Timing (PNT) Service (GPNTS) budget provides for the following GPNTS Enhancements for M-GUE and NoGAPSS Upgrades (GPNTS
 eMNu) beginning in FY 2025: Military Code (M-Code) GPS User Equipment (MGUE) Upgrade Kits and Non-GPS Aided Positioning for Surface and Subsurface (NoGAPSS) Upgrade Kits. GPNTS MGUE
 Upgrade Kit equipment addresses obsolescence of the Trimble SAASM Force 524D GPS receivers. The kit is required for each ship to enable M-Code capability and is dependent on the ship class configuration,
 as well as the date of procurement of the original shipset onboard. The GPNTS MGUE Upgrade Kit includes the M-Code GPS User Equipment receiver cards, updated processor boards, human machine
 interface and timing system upgrades or refurbishments. The GPNTS NoGAPSS Upgrade Kit delivers NoGAPSS capability to all GPNTS-equipped ships. The NoGAPSS Upgrade Kit addresses obsolescence of
 hardware components onboard ships equipped with GPNTS shipsets procured before FY21. The GPNTS NoGAPSS Upgrade kit includes hardware components that were integrated into the GPNTS Technical
 Data Package (TDP) starting in FY 2021 to resolve urgent obsolescence issues and enable GPNTS to support NoGAPSS capability. The GPNTS NoGAPSS Upgrade Kits in this budget will also include the M-
 Code GPS User Equipment receiver cards. The fielding plan for GPNTS MGUE and NoGAPSS Upgrade Kits is determined by the suitable availability periods for ships requiring the upgrade.

 In FY 2027, GPNTS will procure eleven (11) Full Rate Production (FRP) units, of which four (4) are for MSC platforms. In addition, FY 2027 will procure four (4) GPNTS Enhancements for M-GUE and NoGAPSS
 Upgrades (GPNTS eMNu) to include Military Code (M-Code) GPS User Equipment (MGUE) Upgrade Kits and Non-GPS Aided Positioning for Surface and Subsurface (NoGAPSS) Upgrade Kit. The budget
 reflects an average unit cost for these upgrades, calculated per system. The average cost for GPNTS Enhancements for M-GUE upgrades is estimated to be approximately $25,500. The NoGAPSS Upgrades is
 estimated at approximately $500,000 per system. FY27 plans include upgrading 2 MGUE and 2 NoGAPSS (backfit) systems, for a total of 4 upgrades.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                            Date: April 2026
