INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1109_L011$$, 2027, $$The Javelin Missile system delivers a decisive tactical advantage to the Marine Corps, providing a man-portable, fire-and-forget capability that is essential for modern warfare. It is a critical tool that guarantees
 infantry survivability and lethality against a wide spectrum of threats, from advanced armored vehicles to fortified enemy positions.

 The system's combat-proven effectiveness is unmatched. Javelin neutralizes targets at extended ranges in any operational environment, including day, night, and adverse weather conditions. Its performance is
 unimpeded by battlefield obscurants or enemy countermeasures. The "fire-and-forget" technology is a key force multiplier, enabling the gunner to engage a target and immediately relocate, drastically increasing
 survivability in high-threat situations.

 Key advantages of the Javelin system include:
 - A tandem warhead which is engineered to defeat all current and emerging armor threats, ensuring Marine forces maintain battlefield superiority.
 - A soft-launch feature which allows for safe deployment from enclosures and complex urban terrain, providing unparalleled tactical flexibility.
 - A modular Lightweight Command Launch Unit (LWCLU) architecture which allows for rapid and cost-effective software and hardware upgrades to counter evolving enemy capabilities.
 - A Block I missile variant which further increases the probability of mission success with improved range, a more lethal warhead, and a reduced time-of-flight to the target.

 As a joint program between the Marine Corps and the U.S. Army, the Javelin represents a cornerstone of Marine ground forces' combat power. Its continued support and modernization are a direct investment in
 the survivability of warfighters and their ability to dominate any adversary on the battlefield.$$, $$$$, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                                   Date: April 2026
